T*
T*
(Preserving Experience, Growing People, Building Better Teams) Tj
T*
T*
(## Opening) Tj
T*
T*
(Good morning everyone, and thank you for joining this Knowledge Sharing Session.) Tj
T*
T*
(Today I want to talk about something that I believe is very important in every organization,) Tj
T*
(and that is the conservation of knowledge.) Tj
T*
T*
(When I say “conservation of knowledge,” I do not mean keeping knowledge to ourselves. I mean) Tj
T*
(preserving what we know, sharing it wisely, passing it on, and making sure that experience) Tj
T*
(does not disappear when a person leaves a team, changes role, or moves on.) Tj
T*
T*
(In every workplace, people gather experience over time. People learn shortcuts, discover) Tj
T*
(better ways of doing things, understand how to handle difficult situations, and develop) Tj
T*
(judgment that cannot always be found in manuals. If that knowledge stays only in one) Tj
T*
(person’s head, then the organization is always at risk. But when knowledge is shared,) Tj
T*
(documented, and passed down, the whole team becomes stronger.) Tj
T*
T*
(So today, I want us to think about knowledge not just as information, but as something) Tj
T*
(valuable that must be protected, shared, and transferred from one person to another.) Tj
T*
T*
(This session will focus on a few important ideas:) Tj
T*
T*
(- Learning from the knowledge and experience of others - Tapping into mentorship, whether) Tj
T*
(  formal or informal - Conserving knowledge so it is not lost when people leave - Learning) Tj
T*
(  how to give and receive feedback well - Making people feel seen, valued, and recognized) Tj
T*
(  for what they contribute) Tj
T*
T*
(I hope by the end of this session, we will all see knowledge sharing a little differently —) Tj
T*
(not just as a nice workplace habit, but as something that helps teams grow, helps people) Tj
T*
(improve, and helps organizations become more resilient.) Tj
T*
T*
(## 1. What “Conservation of Knowledge” Means) Tj
T*
T*
(Let me start by explaining the title.) Tj
T*
T*
(When we hear the word “conservation,” we often think of preserving something valuable so it) Tj
T*
(does not get wasted or lost. In this case, what we are preserving is knowledge. And) Tj
T*
(knowledge in the workplace is not just facts or training materials. It includes experience,) Tj
T*
(judgment, good practices, lessons learned, problem-solving skills, and even the small things) Tj
T*
(people discover along the way that make work easier and better.) Tj
T*
T*
(A lot of times, in organizations, there are people who know how to do certain things so well) Tj
T*
