(## 4. Why Knowledge Must Be Passed On) Tj
T*
T*
(Let us talk a little more about why knowledge transfer is so important.) Tj
T*
T*
(In many teams, you will find that one person knows how to do something very well, and) Tj
T*
(everybody else depends on that person. That may sound good in the short term because the) Tj
T*
(person is reliable. But in the long term, it becomes a problem.) Tj
T*
T*
(Why?) Tj
T*
T*
(Because if everything depends on one person, then the team becomes fragile. The moment that) Tj
T*
(person is unavailable, work slows down. People begin to struggle. The team loses time.) Tj
T*
(Sometimes, people even make avoidable mistakes because they did not have access to the right) Tj
T*
(knowledge.) Tj
T*
T*
(That is why knowledge transfer is not optional. It is part of building a sustainable) Tj
T*
(organization.) Tj
T*
T*
(When people share what they know, they are not making themselves less valuable. In fact,) Tj
T*
(they are making the whole team more capable. And that is a better form of value. It means) Tj
T*
(the work does not sit in one head. It becomes shared capability.) Tj
T*
T*
(This is very important for onboarding too.) Tj
T*
T*
(When a new person joins a team, they should not have to discover everything alone. They) Tj
T*
(should be able to benefit from the knowledge that others already carry. That could come) Tj
T*
(through conversations, checklists, guides, recorded walkthroughs, mentoring, or simply) Tj
T*
(someone taking time to explain how things work.) Tj
T*
T*
(The faster a person understands the environment, the faster they can contribute. And the) Tj
T*
(faster the team gets value from that person.) Tj
T*
T*
(So knowledge conservation is not only about protecting what we already know. It is also) Tj
T*
(about helping new people become effective faster.) Tj
T*
T*
(## 5. The Role of Feedback in Preserving Knowledge) Tj
T*
T*
(Now let us move to feedback.) Tj
T*
T*
(Feedback is one of the most powerful tools for growth, but it is often misunderstood. Some) Tj
T*
(people hear feedback and immediately think of criticism. Others hear feedback and feel) Tj
T*
(attacked. But feedback does not have to be negative. In fact, good feedback is one of the) Tj
T*
(ways knowledge is preserved and improved.) Tj
T*
T*
(Why do I say that?) Tj
T*
T*
ET
